ps.  Shego passes under Kim.<br/><br/><img src="images/asit_present/253.jpg" alt="[image] " border="0"/><br/>Shego slashes a nearby tree.  It falls on top of Kim.  Fortunaely she is unhurt.<br/><br/><img src="images/asit_present/254.jpg" alt="[image] " border="0"/><br/>Kim watches as Shego runs back to the plane.<br/><br/><img src="images/asit_present/255.jpg" alt="[image] " border="0"/><br/>Kim then sees Monkey Fist with the head of the tempus simia.<br/><br/><img src="images/asit_present/256.jpg" alt="[image] " border="0"/><br/>Monkey Fist jumps to the top of a rock to await his flight.<br/><br/><img src="images/asit_present/257.jpg" alt="[image] " border="0"/><br/>Shego is the pilot, but may have other ways to navigate the aircraft.  It could be done with a remote control or voice activation.  As mentioned before, the aircraft is capable of verticle takeoffs and landings.<br/><br/><img src="images/asit_present/258.jpg" alt="[image] " border="0"/><br/>Once Monkey Fist is inside, the plane takes off going straight up.<br/><br/><img src="images/asit_present/259.jpg" alt="[image] " border="0"/><br/>Monique indicates she likes the land surfing part of the mission, but not the fighting.<br/><br/><img src="images/asit_present/260.jpg" alt="[image] " border="0"/><br/>Ron suddenly arrives by parachute, and does a perfect landing.<br/><br/><img src="images/asit_present/261.jpg" alt="[image] " border="0"/><br/>Ron sees the carnage and realizes that he is too late.<br/><br/><img src="images/asit_present/262.jpg" alt="[image] " border="0"/><br/>Kim is disappointed that Team Drakken have both the tempus simia and the missing head.<br/><br/>









